{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":840,"text":"In 2008, Burhan Hassan, age 17,"},{"time":4960,"text":"boarded a flight from Minneapolis"},{"time":6920,"text":"to the Horn of Africa."},{"time":9240,"text":"And while Burhan was the youngest recruit,"},{"time":11680,"text":"he was not alone."},{"time":13360,"text":"Al-Shabaab managed to recruit\nover two dozen young men"},{"time":16760,"text":"in their late teens and early 20s"},{"time":19360,"text":"with a heavy presence\non social media platforms like Facebook."},{"time":23400,"text":"With the Internet and other technologies,"},{"time":25680,"text":"they've changed our everyday lives,"},{"time":27400,"text":"but they've also changed\nrecruitment, radicalization"},{"time":31240,"text":"and the front lines of conflict today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35680,"text":"What about the links connecting Twitter,"},{"time":38160,"text":"Google and protesters\nfighting for democracy?"},{"time":42120,"text":"These numbers represent\nGoogle's public DNS servers,"},{"time":46160,"text":"effectively the only\ndigital border crossing"},{"time":48720,"text":"protesters had and could use"},{"time":50800,"text":"to communicate with each other,\nto reach the outside world"},{"time":53640,"text":"and to spread viral awareness"},{"time":55280,"text":"of what was happening\nin their own country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58960,"text":"Today, conflict is essentially borderless."},{"time":61400,"text":"If there are bounds to conflict today,"},{"time":64080,"text":"they're bound by digital,\nnot physical geography."},{"time":68000,"text":"And under all this is a vacuum of power"},{"time":71080,"text":"where non-state actors, individuals\nand private organizations"},{"time":75160,"text":"have the advantage over slow, outdated\nmilitary and intelligence agencies."},{"time":81240,"text":"And this is because,\nin the digital age of conflict,"},{"time":84040,"text":"there exists a feedback loop"},{"time":86320,"text":"where new technologies,\nplatforms like the ones I mentioned,"},{"time":89200,"text":"and more disruptive ones,"},{"time":90680,"text":"can be adapted, learned, and deployed\nby individuals and organizations"},{"time":95480,"text":"faster than governments can react."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99840,"text":"To understand the pace\nof our own government thinking on this,"},{"time":103960,"text":"I like to turn to something aptly named"},{"time":105960,"text":"the Worldwide Threat Assessment,"},{"time":109120,"text":"where every year the Director\nof National Intelligence in the US"},{"time":112840,"text":"looks at the global threat landscape,"},{"time":115680,"text":"and he says, \"These are the threats,\nthese are the details,"},{"time":118960,"text":"and this is how we rank them.\""},{"time":121040,"text":"In 2007, there was absolutely\nno mention of cyber security."},{"time":124480,"text":"It took until 2011,\nwhen it came at the end,"},{"time":128199,"text":"where other things, like West\nAfrican drug trafficking, took precedence."},{"time":132120,"text":"In 2012, it crept up, still behind things\nlike terrorism and proliferation."},{"time":137640,"text":"In 2013, it became the top threat,"},{"time":139760,"text":"in 2014 and for the foreseeable future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144240,"text":"What things like that show us"},{"time":145920,"text":"is that there is\na fundamental inability today"},{"time":148920,"text":"on the part of governments\nto adapt and learn in digital conflict,"},{"time":154120,"text":"where conflict can be immaterial,\nborderless, often wholly untraceable."},{"time":159560,"text":"And conflict isn't just online to offline,\nas we see with terrorist radicalization,"},{"time":164200,"text":"but it goes the other way as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167520,"text":"We all know the horrible events\nthat unfolded in Paris this year"},{"time":171080,"text":"with the Charlie Hebdo terrorist attacks."},{"time":173057,"text":"What an individual hacker or a small group\nof anonymous individuals did"},{"time":177560,"text":"was enter those social media conversations\nthat so many of us took part in."},{"time":182200,"text":"#JeSuisCharlie."},{"time":184360,"text":"On Facebook, on Twitter, on Google,"},{"time":186600,"text":"all sorts of places where millions\nof people, myself included,"},{"time":190080,"text":"were talking about the events"},{"time":191720,"text":"and saw images like this,"},{"time":193200,"text":"the emotional, poignant image of a baby\nwith \"Je suis Charlie\" on its wrist."},{"time":198360,"text":"And this turned into a weapon."},{"time":200480,"text":"What the hackers did\nwas weaponize this image,"},{"time":202840,"text":"where unsuspecting victims,"},{"time":204520,"text":"like all of us in those conversations,"},{"time":206440,"text":"saw this image, downloaded it"},{"time":209080,"text":"but it was embedded with malware."},{"time":211240,"text":"And so when you downloaded this image,"},{"time":213240,"text":"it hacked your system."},{"time":215320,"text":"It took six days to deploy\na global malware campaign."},{"time":220400,"text":"The divide between physical\nand digital domains today"},{"time":223160,"text":"ceases to exist,"},{"time":224600,"text":"where we have offline attacks\nlike those in Paris"},{"time":227560,"text":"appropriated for online hacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231320,"text":"And it goes the other way as well,\nwith recruitment."},{"time":233800,"text":"We see online radicalization of teens,"},{"time":236280,"text":"who can then be deployed globally\nfor offline terrorist attacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241480,"text":"With all of this, we see that there's\na new 21st century battle brewing,"},{"time":246360,"text":"and governments\ndon't necessarily take a part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249560,"text":"So in another case,\nAnonymous vs. Los Zetas."},{"time":254920,"text":"In early September 2011 in Mexico,"},{"time":257480,"text":"Los Zetas, one of the most\npowerful drug cartels,"},{"time":260560,"text":"hung two bloggers with a sign that said,"},{"time":262920,"text":"\"This is what will happen\nto all Internet busybodies.\""},{"time":267720,"text":"A week later, they beheaded a young girl."},{"time":269720,"text":"They severed her head,\nput it on top of her computer"},{"time":272200,"text":"with a similar note."},{"time":273440,"text":"And taking the digital counteroffensive"},{"time":276320,"text":"because governments couldn't even\nunderstand what was going on or act,"},{"time":279630,"text":"Anonymous, a group we might not associate\nas the most positive force in the world,"},{"time":283550,"text":"took action,"},{"time":284760,"text":"not in cyber attacks, but threatening\ninformation to be free."},{"time":289920,"text":"On social media, they said,"},{"time":291640,"text":"\"We will release information"},{"time":293320,"text":"that ties prosecutors and governors\nto corrupt drug deals with the cartel.\""},{"time":298800,"text":"And escalating that conflict,"},{"time":301200,"text":"Los Zetas said, \"We will kill 10 people\nfor every bit of information you release.\""},{"time":307880,"text":"And so it ended there because\nit would become too gruesome to continue."},{"time":313560,"text":"But what was powerful about this"},{"time":316640,"text":"was that anonymous individuals,"},{"time":319240,"text":"not federal policia,\nnot military, not politicians,"},{"time":322880,"text":"could strike fear deep into the heart"},{"time":327080,"text":"of one of the most powerful,\nviolent organizations in the world."},{"time":332320,"text":"And so we live in an era"},{"time":334520,"text":"that lacks the clarity\nof the past in conflict,"},{"time":338080,"text":"in who we're fighting,\nin the motivations behind attacks,"},{"time":341920,"text":"in the tools and techniques used,"},{"time":343800,"text":"and how quickly they evolve."},{"time":346720,"text":"And the question still remains:"},{"time":348240,"text":"what can individuals,\norganizations and governments do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353800,"text":"For answers to these questions,\nit starts with individuals,"},{"time":356640,"text":"and I think peer-to-peer security\nis the answer."},{"time":360800,"text":"Those people in relationships\nthat bought over teens online,"},{"time":364760,"text":"we can do that with peer-to-peer security."},{"time":366840,"text":"Individuals have more power\nthan ever before"},{"time":369400,"text":"to affect national\nand international security."},{"time":373360,"text":"And we can create those positive\npeer-to-peer relationships"},{"time":376640,"text":"on and offline,"},{"time":378720,"text":"we can support and educate the next\ngeneration of hackers, like myself,"},{"time":383080,"text":"instead of saying, \"You can either be\na criminal or join the NSA.\""},{"time":387360,"text":"That matters today."},{"time":389840,"text":"And it's not just individuals --\nit's organizations, corporations even."},{"time":395160,"text":"They have an advantage\nto act across more borders,"},{"time":397720,"text":"more effectively and more rapidly\nthan governments can,"},{"time":401280,"text":"and there's a set\nof real incentives there."},{"time":405440,"text":"It's profitable and valuable"},{"time":407160,"text":"to be seen as trustworthy\nin the digital age,"},{"time":410680,"text":"and will only be more so\nin future generations to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414680,"text":"But we still can't ignore government,"},{"time":416520,"text":"because that's who we turn to\nfor collective action"},{"time":419880,"text":"to keep us safe and secure."},{"time":424080,"text":"But we see where that's gotten us so far,"},{"time":427120,"text":"where there's an inability to adapt\nand learn in digital conflict,"},{"time":430880,"text":"where at the highest levels of leadership,"},{"time":433960,"text":"the Director of the CIA,\nSecretary of Defense,"},{"time":436360,"text":"they say, \"Cyber Pearl Harbor will happen.\"\n\"Cyber 9/11 is imminent.\""},{"time":443080,"text":"But this only makes us\nmore fearful, not more secure."},{"time":447200,"text":"By banning encryption in favor\nof mass surveillance and mass hacking,"},{"time":450960,"text":"sure, GCHQ and the NSA can spy on you."},{"time":454880,"text":"But that doesn't mean\nthat they're the only ones that can."},{"time":457619,"text":"Capabilities are cheap, even free."},{"time":459800,"text":"Technical ability\nis rising around the world,"},{"time":462440,"text":"and individuals and small groups\nhave the advantage."},{"time":467520,"text":"So today it might just be\nthe NSA and GCHQ,"},{"time":470480,"text":"but who's to say that the Chinese\ncan't find that backdoor?"},{"time":474120,"text":"Or in another generation,\nsome kid in his basement in Estonia?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":478880,"text":"And so I would say that it's\nnot what governments can do,"},{"time":483680,"text":"it's that they can't."},{"time":485720,"text":"Governments today\nneed to give up power and control"},{"time":490240,"text":"in order to help make us more secure."},{"time":493600,"text":"Giving up mass surveillance and hacking\nand instead fixing those backdoors"},{"time":497720,"text":"means that, yeah, they can't spy on us,"},{"time":500000,"text":"but neither can the Chinese"},{"time":501360,"text":"or that hacker in Estonia\na generation from now."},{"time":505280,"text":"And government support\nfor technologies like Tor and Bitcoin"},{"time":508760,"text":"mean giving up control,"},{"time":510360,"text":"but it means that developers, translators,\nanybody with an Internet connection,"},{"time":514679,"text":"in countries like Cuba, Iran and China,\ncan sell their skills, their products,"},{"time":518799,"text":"in the global marketplace,"},{"time":520200,"text":"but more importantly sell their ideas,"},{"time":522440,"text":"show us what's happening\nin their own countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526080,"text":"And so it should be not fearful,"},{"time":528400,"text":"it should be inspiring\nto the same governments"},{"time":530840,"text":"that fought for civil rights,\nfree speech and democracy"},{"time":533720,"text":"in the great wars of the last century,"},{"time":535760,"text":"that today, for the first time\nin human history,"},{"time":538840,"text":"we have a technical opportunity"},{"time":541080,"text":"to make billions of people\nsafer around the world"},{"time":543720,"text":"that we've never had before\nin human history."},{"time":546280,"text":"It should be inspiring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549840,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}